From 0c5627ec029838efba54882e0b92e2f007419d52 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 10:49:09 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/panel: novatek-nt36672e: add Gemini descriptor

Extend the shared NT36672E framework with descriptor-selected supplies,
reset/power timing, and suspend delays while preserving the existing
variant.
Add the Gemini 1080x2160 mode and the panel-specific table recovered from
the pinned Planet vendor object. Document the board-specific compatible and
its two provisional bias supplies without asserting a TPS65132 silicon
identity.

The vendor's page-0x10 DCS sleep/display commands remain owned by the
shared framework so the descriptor controls their delays. The Gemini panel
consumer stays disabled until reset and bias behavior are verified on
hardware.

Signed-off-by: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
---
